<FIRST>r a AM-RocketAccident     02-09 0134</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Rocket Accident,0140</SECOND>
<HEAD>Rocket Kills One During Test</HEAD>
<DATELINE>PUEBLO, Colo. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A rocket nose cone apparently being tested
under high air pressure blasted through a factory building's ceiling
Wednesday night and crashed in a parking lot, killing one employee,
police said.
   The 17,000-pound nose cone went through the Kaiser Aerotech
building at the Airport Industrial Park and lodged 4 feet into the
parking lot, Police Sgt. Robert Williams said.
   ``I'd never seen anything like that,'' he said.
   A 66-year-old man who worked at Kaiser Aerotech was killed,
Williams said.
   An explosion occurred when the air pressure was released, but
there was no fire, Williams said.
   ``From what I could determine ... they were testing a rocket cone
under high pressure and something didn't jive quite right and it
became disconnected,'' Williams said.
</TEXT>
