<HEAD>10-Year T-Bills Down</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Yields on 10-year Treasury notes fell to the
lowest level since February 1988.
   The average yield was in Wednesday's auction 8.91 percent, down
from 8.94 percent at the last auction on Nov. 9, 1988.
   It was the lowest rate since 10-year notes averaged 8.21 percent
on Feb. 3, 1988. The notes will carry a coupon interest rate of 8~
percent with each $10,000 in face value selling for $9,977.10.
   A total of $9.5 billion in notes were sold out of bids totaling
$22.7 billion.
