<HEAD>Three Injured By Bomb Blast</HEAD>
<DATELINE>DURBAN, South Africa (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A bomb exploded today in a moving
police van, slightly injuring two officers in the vehicle and a
schoolboy walking nearby, police said.
   The three whites were treated at a hospital and discharged. The
windows of the van were shattered.
   Police said the bomb was believed to be a mini-limpet mine, a
device frequently used by guerrillas of the African National
Congress in their sabotage and bombing campaign against the white
minority government.
   There was no claim of responsibility for the bombing, and police
did not say who was believed responsible.
