<FIRST>d a PM-BRF--CandyCaneMurder     02-09 0153</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-BRF--Candy Cane Murder,0154</SECOND>
<HEAD>Man Gets 70 Years For Killing Candy Company Owner</HEAD>
<DATELINE>TARBORO, N.C. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A man who pleaded guilty to killing the
owner of a candy company by hitting him over the head with a giant
candy cane and strangling him has been sentenced to 70 years in
prison.
   Donald Morris Smith, 22, was sentenced Tuesday to 50 years for
second-degree murder and 20 years for robbery in Edgecombe County
Superior Court.
   Charles W. Doak, 69, owner of the Wilson Candy Co. in nearby
Rocky Mount in east North Carolina, was hit several times over the
head with a nine-pound, 2{-foot candy cane, said Rocky Mount Police
Detective Philip Lane. Lane said the candy cane, which was 5{ inches
in diameter, was on display at the company.
   Dr. R. Patrick Dorion, a pathologist at Nash General Hospital,
said Doak died from a combination of the head wounds and
strangulation.
</TEXT>
