<HEAD>Fire In TV Studio Kills 36, Injures 55</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW DELHI, India (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A fire at a television studio in southern
India killed at least 36 people and injured at least 55, including
one of India's best known actors, a new agency reported today.
   The fire on Wednesday destroyed the studio near Bangalore, 1,100
miles south of New Delhi, United News of India said.
   The studio was filled with actors and technicians filming a
television show. The injured included Sanjay Khan, a well-known
actor and director, who received burns over 60 percent of his body,
the news agency said.
   There was no word on the cause of the fire.
