<HEAD>Pollard's Wife Is Refusing Treatment, Doctor Says</HEAD>
<HEAD>Eds: LEADS with 4 grafs to CLARIFY lawsuit's objective; PICK UP 7th
graf pvs, `Grogan testified ...'</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By BETSY HENDERSON</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>ROCHESTER, Minn. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The wife of spy Jonathan Pollard has
refused medication, slowed her intake of food and worsened an eye
injury by rubbing it, the medical director of a federal
prison-hospital testified today.
   ``In the long term, it is Mrs. Pollard that needs to seek
psychological care,'' Dr. Martha Grogan of the Federal Medical
Center said at a hearing on whether Anne Henderson-Pollard is
getting adequate care for several painful conditions.
   Jonathan Pollard, 34, was convicted in 1987 of supplying
classified U.S. documents to Israeli agents and is serving a life
sentence in a prison in Marion, Ill. His wife, 28, is serving five
years as as an accessory to his possession of the documents.
   Henderson-Pollard, who according to court papers suffers from
gastrointestinal disorders, an ovarian cyst and endometriosis, which
can cause chronic pelvic pain, has filed a lawsuit seeking the
appointment of an independent medical consultant to examine her and
determine what care is needed.
   Grogan testified that Henderson-Pollard has refused to be
examined in order to be referred to specialists. She said that
Henderson-Pollard is confused and that it is not in the woman's
interest for the medical center give in to her demands.
   Henderson-Pollard's lawyer, Hamilton Fox, asked Grogan, ``Would
you allow her to lose her sight if she refused to be treated by
you?''
   Grogan answered that it's a simple matter to get a referral and
that's how the medical center operates.
   Henderson-Pollard's father, Bernard Henderson, said his daughter
had been treated for conditions that prevented food from passing
through her system.
   ``I've seen my beautiful, young daughter who's a shell now,'' he
said. `She walks stooped over and weighs only about 91 pounds.''
</TEXT>
