<HEAD>Australian Pair Are Fastest in Empire State Building Race</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Two Australians streaked up the stairs ahead of
seven dozen other contestants Thursday to win the 12th annual Empire
State Building Run-up.
   Suzanne Malaxos, 27, a teacher from Perth, set a women's record
at 12 minutes 24 seconds. The previous record was 13 minutes 14
seconds, set in 1985 by Janine Aiello, who finished second Thursday.
   Robin Rishworth, 23, a draftsman from Melbourne, won the men's
competition in 11 minutes 8 seconds, nine seconds behind the record.
   Both winners were making their first appearance in the Empire
State Building Run-up. They prepped for the 86-story, 1,575-step
vertical charge by winning the Australian version of the run-up last
year at the 56-story Rialto hotel in Melbourne.
