<SECOND>AM-Treasury Auction,90</SECOND>
<HEAD>30-Year T-Bills Down</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Yields on 30-year Treasury bonds fell in
Thursday's auction to the lowest level since August 1987.
   The average yield was 8.91 percent, down from 9.10 percent at the
last auction on Nov. 17, 1988.
   It was the lowest rate since 30-year bonds averaged 8.89 percent
on Aug. 13, 1987. The bonds will carry a coupon interest rate of 8~
percent with each $10,000 in face value selling for $9,963.60.
   A total of $9.5 billion in bonds were sold out of bids totaling
$17.2 billion.
