<FIRST>r i AM-BRF--Spain-Drought     02-09 0117</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-BRF--Spain-Drought,0120</SECOND>
<HEAD>Drought Expected to Keep Hold on Northern Spain</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MADRID, Spain (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A four-month drought that has dried up fresh
water reserves will keep its grip on northern Spain at least 10 more
days, a forecaster said Thursday.
   The drought, caused by a persistent high-pressure zone that has
affected much of Europe, has reduced rainfall in northern Spain to
between 25 percent and 35 percent of normally dry levels in the last
four months.
   It has also delayed germination of some grain crops.
   The chairman of the National Meteorological Institute, Manuel
Bautista Perez, said a 10-day forecast predicts light rains will
stop this weekend and no more rain is in sight during the period.
</TEXT>
