<FIRST>r w AM-Crops-Oranges     02-09 0133</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Crops-Oranges,130</SECOND>
<HEAD>See More Oranges</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The nation's orange harvest for the 1988-89
season is estimated at about 215 million boxes, virtually unchanged
from the previous forecast a month ago but 7 percent more than last
season, the Agriculture Department said Thursday.
   The Florida crop, based on Feb. 1 indications, was estimated at
150 million boxes, unchanged from last month but 9 percent more than
in 1987-88.
   California production was forecast at 61 million boxes, the same
as in January but 4 percent more than a year ago. The Arizona crop
was forecast at 2 million boxes, unchanged from January and up 10
percent from last season. The Texas harvest, at 1.85 million boxes,
was indicated at 6 percent more than the January forecast and up 29
percent from 1987-88.
