   Organized crime will dominate all gambling on
Indian reservations in 10 years unless the federal government acts
swiftly, a former Mafia figure who ran tribal bingo games contends.
   ``Anytime there's easy money, the mob will jump in,'' said the
witness, who wore a gray hood and testified behind a screen in his
