<FILEID>AP-NR-02-09-89 1246EST</FILEID>
<FIRST>u f PM-Braniff     02-09 0296</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-Braniff,0307</SECOND>
<HEAD>Braniff Headquarters Moving To Florida, Chairman Says</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By IKE FLORES</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>ORLANDO, Fla. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Braniff Inc. will move its headquarters from
Dallas to Orlando beginning in May, Braniff Chairman William McGee
announced today.
   The headquarters move had been expected since the airline was
purchased by a Philadelphia and New York investment group last
summer, and speculation on the location had centered on Kansas City,
Mo., and Orlando, where Braniff has hubs.
   ``As a `new' airline, we have an opportunity to use our
headquarters location to make a statement about our desire to
participate in the growth of one of the fastest-developing regions
in the U.S.,'' McGee said.
   ``Although Kansas City is and will remain our largest hub, our
decision to locate our headquarters here signals our commitment to
the growth of Central Florida as well,'' McGee told a news
conference in Orlando.
   Braniff moved its principal hub operation from Dallas-Fort Worth
International Airport to Kansas City last year.
   The relocation of Braniff headquarters to Orlando will involve
the transfer of about 125 professional and administrative personnel,
McGee said.
   Braniff has about 720 employees in the Orlando area, and McGee
said he expects employment there to grow by more than 425 jobs in
the coming year.
   The company earlier this month leased more than 26,000 square
feet in an abandoned terminal at the Orlando airport.
   BIA Acquisitions, an investor group formed by PaineWebber Inc.,
bought Braniff in June for about $100 million and became the
airline's third owner since its 1982 bankruptcy reorganization.
   The new owners immediately began an effort to rejoin the ranks of
the nation's largest carriers, and the airline recently announced
the purchase of 50 Airbus A300 planes, a $3.5 billion deal that
would nearly double Braniff's fleet.
</TEXT>
</DOC>
