<SECOND>BC-Auto Prodn,0153</SECOND>
<HEAD>Auto Production Goes Down This Week</HEAD>
<DATELINE>DETROIT (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Domestic automakers were scheduled to produce
242,951 cars and light trucks this week, down from last week's
249,649, Ward's Automotive Reports said Thursday.
   This week's production is higher than the same week a year ago,
in which 215,166 cars and light trucks were produced, the trade
journal said.
   U.S. automakers were scheduled to make 153,747 cars this week,
compared with 155,382 a week ago and 134,367 in the same week in
1988.
   Light truck production for the week was scheduled at 89,204,
compared with last week's 94,267 and last year's 80,799.
   Canadian automakers were to build 21,749 cars this week, up from
20,509 a week ago and from last year's 21,739.
   Canadian light truck production was scheduled at 21,632, compared
with 21,679 a week ago and 18,886 in the same week last year.
</TEXT>
