<HEAD>Mazda Dropping Garner As Spokesman</HEAD>
<DATELINE>CHICAGO (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Actor James Garner will be dropped as a spokesman
for Mazda Motor Corp. cars and trucks, a company official said
Thursday.
   Garner, whose contract expires in March, has been the primary
spokesman for the Japanese vehicle maker's full line of cars and
trucks since 1985.
   George McCabe, vice president of Mazda sales and marketing in the
United States, said the automaker is beginning a new advertising
concept.
