<FIRST>r f AM-InsultSoftware     02-09 0179</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Insult Software,0185</SECOND>
<HEAD>Try This Program, You Blob of Freeze-Dried Fish Lips</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A free computer program that can generate 22
million insults has won the seal of approval of an organization
devoted to the art of curses, slurs and maledictions.
   The program, Insults, combines and re-combines about 400 choice
words to produce PG-rated phrases like: ``You revolting box of fresh
bug parts,'' and, ``You skaggy bucket of infested parrot droppings.''
   Dale McKinnon, the author, said Thursday he had upgraded Insults
several times since its publication in 1983 and won the Maledicta
Seal of Approval with the current release, which was completed last
month.
   ```Insults' is a fountain of millions of high-quality insults,''
Dr. Reinhold Aman, president of the International Maledicta Society
of Waukesha, Wis., said in a statement endorsing the program.
   Insults, which is only for IBM and IBM-compatible personal
computers, is available free on computer bulletin boards and from PC
clubs. McKinnon said he charges $5 for handling if people order it
through his Salt Lake City computer consulting service, Modern
Advisory Institute.
</TEXT>
