<DATELINE>CHICAGO (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Wheat and oat futures prices closed lower Thursday
on the Chicago Board of Trade while corn and soybeans finished
little changed in dull trading ahead of an Agriculture Department
grain supply-and-demand report.
   The report, scheduled for release after the close, was expected
to contain lower estimates for Soviet grain and Argentine soybean
production and a higher estimate for the Brazilian soybean crop.
   Analysts said there were no significant supply-and-demand
developments during the session and prices drifted with no firm
direction.
