<SECOND>AM-Electronics Sales,0122</SECOND>
<HEAD>U.S. Sales Of Electronics Rose 9.3 Percent In 1988</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   U.S. companies' worldwide sales of electronic
products and services rose 9.3 percent last year, led by growth in
computers and components, the American Electronics Association said
Thursday.
   Annual sales rose to $278.9 billion in 1988 from $255.2 billion
in 1987, according to the organization, whose figures are based on
Commerce Department data.
   By segment, sales rose 16.1 percent in computers; rose 12.9
percent in components, which includes semiconductors; rose 1.6
percent in telecommunications; and fell 4 percent in consumer
products, the smallest category, the association said.
   In December alone, overall sales rose 9.1 percent to $27.6
billion from $25.3 billion.
